1
00:01:15,960 --> 00:01:17,520
All the colleagues in the department dislike you.

2
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:18,720
Is there something wrong with you?

3
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:20,080
The door lock is rusty.

4
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:22,360
It's been so many years.

5
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:23,360
Haven't you been back at all?

6
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:25,200
The company will still run fine without you.

7
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:25,920
It is just your salary.

8
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:26,840
Don't be so stubborn.

9
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:27,880
What a good girl.

10
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:28,680
Ren Zhen.

11
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:30,039
Join us.

12
00:01:34,479 --> 00:01:35,520
Who is it?

13
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:45,000
Happy Eid al-Adha, Sister.

14
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:46,800
What festival?

15
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:47,759
Eid al-Adha.

16
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:50,330
It's like the Spring Festival.

17
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:52,840
Every household slaughters chickens and sheep,

18
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:53,970
puts on new clothes,

19
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:56,050
and visits relatives and friends.

20
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:56,680
By the way.

21
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,640
There's a bonfire party in our village tonight.

22
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,400
Come with us.

23
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,320
No wonder Grandpa Bate

24
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:03,920
was willing to put his sheep in the pen a few days ago.

25
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,080
Happy festival, Secretary.

26
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:06,240
Happy festival.

27
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:07,340
Here you go.

28
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:09,680
Thank you, Secretary.

29
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:11,800
Bye, bye.

30
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:17,820
Did you not sleep well last night?

31
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,160
Here.

32
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:22,880
It's your first time celebrating a festival in Xinjiang.

33
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,520
New clothes and red envelopes

34
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,520
are essential.

35
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,800
You can wear it tonight.

36
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:29,960
Thank you.

37
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:30,880
No problem.

38
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:33,280
I kind of miss Dad Yin.

39
00:02:34,079 --> 00:02:36,120
I just borrowed a car from Wulan's dad.

40
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,850
Let's pick Mr. Yin up together.

41
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:46,320
Dad Yin said he'd wait for us at home.

42
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:50,280
Why are there still unshipped packages?

43
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:51,600
Look closely.

44
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:53,040
Live streaming.

45
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,680
Four of the orders are Mr. Yin's.

46
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:55,840
Let's just give him

47
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,490
a one-click home delivery.

48
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,960
The streamer personally delivering to your door.

49
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,160
What a top-tier perk!

50
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:03,080
Right.

51
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:04,680
Do you want to send your family and friends,

52
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:07,010
and former colleagues some goji berries?

53
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,280
No need.

54
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,200
To this viewer,

55
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,800
your package will be delivered first.

56
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,120
Thanks for your support.

57
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:27,560
Congratulations on your successful first livestream.

58
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,840
Thank you. Put it inside.

59
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:29,900
Okay, give it to me.

60
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,400
I'll go in first.

61
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:31,960
You guys chat.

62
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:32,760
Zhenzhen.

63
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,280
Happy holidays.

64
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,480
Take it.

65
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:40,960
What's wrong?

66
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:42,380
You look a bit down.

67
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:43,840
I'm fine.

68
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,180
Thank you, Dad Yin.

69
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,120
Jiaoli,

70
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:47,840
come, here's one for you.

71
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:48,770
Happy holidays.

72
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,800
No, I'm too old for this.

73
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:53,200
You'll always be a child to your teacher.

74
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,120
Take it.

75
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:55,880
Take it.

76
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,300
Thank you, sir.

77
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,240
Let's go then.

78
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,400
Everyone is waiting for me to bring you over.

79
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,120
No rush.

80
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,720
Come with me to a place first.

81
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,079
So beautiful!

82
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,200
Ren Zhen,

83
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:38,520
what were you doing then?

84
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,640
So beautiful!

85
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:51,360
Slow down.

86
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,490
Mr. Yin, be careful.

87
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,360
Hurry!

88
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,240
Look, there are fish here!

89
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:05,520
Isn't Sayram Lake a saltwater lake?

90
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:06,920
How can there be fish?

91
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:08,480
Our Sayram Lake

92
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,840
is slightly salty.

93
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,000
Lao Guo,

94
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,120
Lao Guo!

95
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,240
We're late.

96
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:24,880
This old guy

97
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:27,500
must have gone back for the festival.

98
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:28,960
Mr. Yin,

99
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:31,250
you know Lao Guo, the peled farmer?

100
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,400
Who is Lao Guo?

101
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:34,560
A fish farmer.

102
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:37,080
Seven years ago,

103
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:39,180
I brought my students here for

104
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,720
a language Nadam,

105
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,409
and that's how I met him.

106
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:45,120
Since then, before every festival,

107
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:46,680
I come to see him.

108
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,680
I was writing lesson plans these days,

109
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,610
so I got delayed.

110
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:52,920
Nadam?

111
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:54,920
What is Nadam?

112
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:56,240
Nadam

113
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,240
is a kind of gathering here.

114
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:00,200
Everyone gets together,

115
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:02,480
rides horses, shoots arrows,

116
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:03,760
and wrestles.

117
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,620
Some play the tovshuur

118
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,120
and sing Mongolian short songs.

119
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,650
Everyone sings and dances.

120
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:10,600
Mr. Yin

121
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,400
wants our language learning

122
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:15,160
to be like a game or a party,

123
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,720
so we can relax

124
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:19,160
while reading and writing on the grassland.

125
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:19,720
This

126
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:22,280
is called the language Nadam.

127
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,200
By the way,

128
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:26,620
you said you saw fish just now?

129
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,600
I just saw some scales.

130
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,160
I knew it.

131
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:32,800
The peled

132
00:06:33,159 --> 00:06:34,920
lives 30 meters underwater.

133
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:37,450
It doesn't easily come out during the day.

134
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:40,080
Sayram Lake wasn't suitable for fish farming.

135
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:42,720
Lao Guo researched for 30 years

136
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,680
and finally succeeded in farming Russian peled

137
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,720
here.

138
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,880
How come I've never heard of it?

139
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,880
It's normal.

140
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:52,090
Many people don't know.

141
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,480
In the northern ocean there is a fish,

142
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,840
its name is peled.

143
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,840
What if we livestream

144
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:58,920
to sell peled?

145
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:03,380
There's no shortage of buyers for Peled.

146
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,160
This kind of fish,

147
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,880
back in Russia,

148
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,520
wasn't very good eating.

149
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:11,240
After Old Guo introduced it here,

150
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,840
the fish grew plump

151
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:14,080
and tasty.

152
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,370
But the yield is extremely low.

153
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:19,040
It takes three years to grow one kilogram.

154
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:20,040
But each kilogram

155
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,720
can sell for over 200 yuan.

156
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,840
Some of the fish

157
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:29,060
are supplied to nearby restaurants and hotels,

158
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,120
and the rest

159
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:32,090
are sent directly to Shanghai.

160
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:34,440
So there's no need to worry about sales.

161
00:07:35,159 --> 00:07:37,200
Producing and selling it themselves. That's great.

162
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,080
In Xinjiang,

163
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:40,760
we have many other great things that are unknown

164
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,800
and have no market.

165
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,370
For example,

166
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,480
brown cattle beef

167
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,860
and mulberry leaf tea.

168
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:50,520
Wouldn't it be great if we could let more people know

169
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:53,320
about Xinjiang's local specialties?

170
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:56,240
Ren Zhen,

171
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,680
what do you think?

172
00:07:58,440 --> 00:07:59,240
This...

173
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:02,090
I haven't thought about it yet.

174
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,460
Then don't think about it.

175
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:06,800
Let's go.

176
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,440
Zhen.

177
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:20,200
Let's go home, Zhen.

178
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:29,640
Mr. Yin is for Xinjiang education aid,

179
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,640
Guo is for fish farming,

180
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:35,280
and Jiao Li wants everyone to live a better life.

181
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:36,799
Ren Zhen.

182
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,159
Why are you here?
